  <summary date="2019-03-13T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Sunshine in the Courtroom Act of 2019

This bill establishes a framework to allow federal court proceedings&#8212;in district courts, in circuit courts, and at the Supreme Court&#8212;to be photographed, recorded, broadcast, or televised.

Specifically, it authorizes the presiding judge to permit media coverage of court proceedings, subject to requirements and limitations.</summary>
